<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1896-01-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1896-01-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="471" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d471">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Knight</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Pretoria</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-01-25"><hi rend="italic">January 25,
                                1896</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Hammond still in prison. Bail refused. His present treatment
                            satisfactory. All other arrested American citizens out of prison on
                            $10,000 bail each, but compelled to remain in Pretoria. Trial not before
                            21 April. All the property shares and bank accounts of the arrested
                            Americans have been attached by Government.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Knight.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>